Package: GLAMMGoF
Title: Resampling-Based Assessment of Generalized Linear and Generalized Additive Model Fit Statistics (RRMSE, RMAE, RMedAE, RBIAS, Brier, and AUC)
Version: 1.0.3
Authors@R: 
    person("Colin", "Shea", , "colin.shea@myfwc.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2906-250X"))
Description: This package takes generalized linear and generalized additive models (with or without random effects) fitted using various packages (glmmTMB, mgcv, stats, lme4, MASS, etc.) to assess in- and out-of-sample predictive performance using either repeated random holdout (Monte Carlo cross-validation) or bootstrap resampling with out-of-bag evaluation. In both cases, models are refit to a training dataset and evaluated on a separate test dataset across nReps replicates, generating a sampling distribution of each performance statistic. For models with a continuous or integer response, the fit statistics are relative root mean squared error (RRMSE), relative mean absolute error (RMAE), relative median absolute error (RMedAE), and relative bias (RBIAS). For binary response models, the fit statistics are Brier scores and AUC statistics. All performance measures are based on population-level predictions (i.e., random effects are ignored when present). Users can optionally use DHARMa package functions to assess model residuals.
